    <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 2026</p>
    <p>These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern your use of PackersHub's website and relocation services. By requesting a quote, booking a move, or otherwise using our services, you agree to these Terms. Please read them carefully. This is a general template and not a substitute for legal advice — PackersHub should have these reviewed by a qualified lawyer for full compliance with applicable Indian law.</p>

    <h2>1. Service Agreement</h2>
    <p>By booking PackersHub services, you agree to the scope of work, pricing, and schedule confirmed at the time of booking, whether by phone, WhatsApp, or our website. Our all-inclusive quotes cover survey, packing material, labour, loading, transport, unloading, and basic goods-in-transit insurance — there are no hidden charges for stairs, elevators, distance within the city, or standard access conditions disclosed at the time of survey. Charges may change if the actual volume, distance, or scope of work at pickup differs materially from what was declared at the time of quotation.</p>

    <h2>2. Booking and Scheduling</h2>
    <p>Bookings are confirmed once a move date, scope, and price are agreed upon. We recommend booking at least 3–5 days in advance for local moves and 1–2 weeks in advance for interstate moves or moves during peak periods. PackersHub will make reasonable efforts to honour the agreed date and time but is not liable for delays caused by traffic, weather, regulatory checkpoints, strikes, or other circumstances beyond our reasonable control (force majeure).</p>

    <h2>3. Cancellation and Rescheduling</h2>
    <p>You may cancel or reschedule a confirmed booking by contacting us at least 24 hours before the scheduled move time, free of charge. Cancellations or rescheduling requests made with less notice may be subject to a partial charge to cover crew and vehicle allocation already committed for that slot — this will be communicated to you at the time of booking confirmation.</p>

    <h2>4. Customer Responsibilities</h2>
    <p>You are responsible for: accurately declaring the volume and nature of items to be moved (including fragile, hazardous, or high-value items); ensuring someone authorised is present at pickup and delivery; and disclosing any access restrictions (narrow lanes, no-lift buildings, security clearances) in advance. PackersHub does not transport prohibited items such as firearms, explosives, illegal substances, or livestock.</p>

    <h2>5. Liability and Insurance</h2>
    <p>Every consignment carries goods-in-transit insurance as standard. In the event of loss or damage during transit, PackersHub's liability is limited to the declared value of the goods as covered under the applicable insurance policy. Claims for damage or loss must be reported in writing (call, WhatsApp, or email) within 24 hours of delivery, accompanied by photographic evidence where possible. PackersHub is not liable for damage to items packed by the customer themselves unless our crew also handled loading, nor for pre-existing damage or normal wear noted at pickup.</p>

    <h2>6. Payment Terms</h2>
    <p>Unless otherwise agreed in writing, full payment is due on completion of the move. We accept UPI, NEFT, Credit/Debit Card, and Cash. For interstate or large-volume moves, an advance booking amount may be requested to confirm the slot, with the balance due on delivery.</p>

    <h2>7. Limitation of Liability</h2>
    <p>To the extent permitted by law, PackersHub's total liability for any claim arising from a booking shall not exceed the total amount paid for that specific move, except in cases of proven gross negligence or wilful misconduct.</p>

    <h2>8. Governing Law</h2>
    <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of India. Any disputes shall be subject to the jurisdiction of the courts at Nellore, Andhra Pradesh.</p>

    <h2>9. Changes to These Terms</h2>
    <p>PackersHub may update these Terms from time to time. The latest version will always be available at this page, with the "Last Updated" date revised accordingly.</p>

